>[Question]
>find the height of a building that casts a 40 foot shadow at a  30 
>degree angle ? I can not figure this out
>
>[Difficulty]
>the whole formula to figure it out
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Hello Steve,

You have a right triangle, with one acute angle 30deg.  The side adjacent to that angle is 
40 ft.  So,  letting h be the height of the building, 

tan(30deg) = h/40.

So,

h=40*tan(30deg).


